                            <comment id="15060360" author="ijuma" created="Wed, 16 Dec 2015 17:30:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report. Is this a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1894&quot; title=&quot;Avoid long or infinite blocking in the consumer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1894&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1894&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15093078" author="hachikuji" created="Tue, 12 Jan 2016 01:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ijuma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ijuma&quot;&gt;ijuma&lt;/a&gt; Maybe we can treat this as a separate issue. It seems common to accidentally point the bootstrap brokers to zookeeper, for example, and the current behavior is to silently retry forever. Maybe we can address the common misconfiguration problem here without needing the full patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1894&quot; title=&quot;Avoid long or infinite blocking in the consumer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1894&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1894&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;? A simple approach might be to log disconnects to any of the bootstrap brokers at the error level.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15093118" author="ijuma" created="Tue, 12 Jan 2016 01:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds like a good plan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
